<item>
            <title>[PDFBOX-412] Failure to render PDFs with embedded fonts</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-412</link>
                <project id="12310760" key="PDFBOX">PDFBox</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Trying to view 2 PDF files in PDFReader, the following problems happen:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;test_openoffice301.pdf : all characters replaced by squares (no error logged)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;test_word+pdfcreator.pdf : fallback to Arial (see log bellow)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;The files were created with OpenOffice 3.0.1 (exported as PDF) and Word (printed to PDF with PDFCreator). They both contain 3 lines of text using the DejaVu open-source font.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;PDFBox version used is trunk from january 28th, 2009:&lt;br/&gt;
fontbox trunk 718464&lt;br/&gt;
jempbox trunk 718464&lt;br/&gt;
pdfbox trunk 737638&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For test_word+pdfcreator.pdf, the following lines are found in log:&lt;/p&gt;

