                            <comment id="12668393" author="lehmi" created="Thu, 29 Jan 2009 10:03:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;After a first look at your documents I came to the following conclusions:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;test_openoffice301.pdf:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;it uses ArialNarrow as font not DejaVu as mentioned&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;the problem seems to be an (unicode-)encoding issue. There are some other jira-issues with similar problems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;test_word+pdfcreator.pdf:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;in some way pdfbox can&apos;t read the embedded font and consequently it throws an exception&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;finally the font isn&apos;t found and the fallback (Arial) is used&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

</comment>
                            <comment id="12670442" author="carrier" created="Wed, 4 Feb 2009 20:12:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I just verified that the text is properly extracted from both files.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m changing the priority of this to Major instead of Blocker because it is not blocking development or causing crashes. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12754705" author="lehmi" created="Sun, 13 Sep 2009 14:49:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;With solving &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-516&quot; title=&quot;Font Manager does not always find correct font from environment&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-516&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-516&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-517&quot; title=&quot;PD Fonts do not attempt to load from the environment if an embed font cannot be loaded&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-517&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-517&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; as a workaround test_word+pdfcreator.pdf renders fine.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13114065" author="qoregexp" created="Sat, 24 Sep 2011 20:06:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Please explain the workaround.  The file bug_example.pdf has an embedded font Bookshelf Symbol 3 and it is a truetype font, but when I run the pdfbox application it gives the message &quot;Changing font on &amp;lt;B&amp;gt; from &amp;lt;Bookshelf Symbol 3&amp;gt; to the default font&quot; (and so on for each character).  I am using version 1.6.0 of the application.  You can open the file in Adobe Reader to see what it&apos;s supposed to look like.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13728823" author="lehmi" created="Sun, 4 Aug 2013 09:55:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;bug_example.pdf and test_openoffice301.pdf are working well after solving &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-490&quot; title=&quot;Pdf Printing of text from embedded fonts&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-490&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-490&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, but there is still an issue with the 3. attached pdf. I guess still a prtoblem with the encoding ...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13734907" author="lehmi" created="Fri, 9 Aug 2013 15:32:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I fixed the encoding issue in revision 1512344.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
